    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "Inequality is obvious for the second claim, the problem is strict inequality. This fails for small $n$, for example\\[\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{1}{3}-\\frac{1}{4}=-\\frac{1}{12}.\\]Arguments of Kovac and van Doorn in the comment section prove a weak version of the first question, with an upper bound of\\[2^{-n\\frac{(\\log\\log\\log n)^{1+o(1)}}{\\log n}},\\]and van Doorn gives a heuristic that suggests this may be the true order of magnitude."
    },
